  <brief_title>Safety and Efficacy of a Novel Malathion Formulation in the Treatment of Head Lice</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multi-Center Phase III Study to Evaluate MALG, a Novel Malathion 0.05%Formulation, for the Control of Head Lice in Pediatric and Adult Subjects With Pediculosis Capitis</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Taro Pharmaceuticals USA</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Taro Pharmaceuticals USA</source>
  <oversight_info>
    <has_dmc>No</has_dmc>
  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Current treatments for head lice include over-the-counter products such as permethrin and
      prescription products such as OVIDE (malathion 0.5%) lotion. In a previous phase II study, a
      novel, easy-to-use malathion 0.5% formulation was found to be a safe treatment for head lice.
      The current study will compare the efficacy and safety of this novel formulation of malathion
      with OVIDE and with an over-the-counter permethrin product.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
